(Docker Guide \(Atho\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Last refresh: 2026-04-14.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Docker in Atho is now build/bootstrap only.) Tj
T*
(Runtime is native on host.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Model) Tj
T*
(- Docker builds pinned binaries and bootstrap metadata in a reproducible Linux toolchain.) Tj
T*
(- Launcher exports those artifacts to local folders.) Tj
T*
(- Node/miner/wallet/gui processes are launched natively \(not in containers\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Prereqs) Tj
T*
(- Docker Desktop \(macOS/Windows\) or Docker Engine \(Linux\).) Tj
T*
(- Host Python environment for runtime \(.venv is managed by launcher unless --skip-pip\).) Tj
T*
(- Full OS package matrix \(including host-native fallback tools\): build-prereqs.md) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(One-Command Usage) Tj
T*
(From repo root:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Option 1 \(recommended\):) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Windows PowerShell equivalent:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Option 2 \(power users\):) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What happens:) Tj
T*
(- run.py launches GUI natively.) Tj
T*
(- If GUI dependencies are missing on the current interpreter, run.py runs build.py once and) Tj
T*
(relaunches GUI from .venv.) Tj
T*
(- GUI checks runtime readiness \(runtime/build_manifest_<network>.json + required binaries/libs\).) Tj
T*
(- If missing, GUI invokes build.py.) Tj
T*
(- build.py runs Docker preflight checks \(binary + daemon\), then calls Docker builder flow) Tj
T*
(\(docker/run.py --mode builder\), exports artifacts, validates output, writes) Tj
T*
(runtime/build_manifest_<network>.json.) Tj
T*
(- If selected network binaries are already present, build.py skips Docker rebuild and only) Tj
T*
(finalizes runtime metadata.) Tj
T*
(- GUI continues with native runtime controls and opens first-run Setup Assistant \(wallet +) Tj
T*
(encryption + node profile\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Useful Flags) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Artifacts and Paths) Tj
T*
(- Docker export root: runtime/docker_bootstrap/) Tj
T*
