(- Export manifest: runtime/docker_bootstrap/bootstrap_manifest.json) Tj
T*
(- In-image metadata: runtime/docker_bootstrap/image/docker_bootstrap/build_manifest.json) Tj
T*
(- Binary destination \(network-scoped\): Binaries/<network>/) Tj
T*
(- Runtime-ready marker: runtime/build_manifest_<network>.json \(legacy) Tj
T*
(runtime/build_manifest.json kept for compatibility\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Runtime Notes) Tj
T*
(- Storage/key/log directories are managed by native runtime logic.) Tj
T*
(- Docker no longer starts/stops node containers and no longer manages compose stacks.) Tj
T*
(- Closing GUI stops native nodes by default \(ATHO_STOP_ON_GUI_EXIT=0 to keep running\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Troubleshooting) Tj
T*
(- docker not found: install Docker Desktop/Engine and restart terminal.) Tj
T*
(- docker daemon unavailable: open Docker Desktop \(or start Docker Engine service\) and wait until) Tj
T*
(engine status is healthy.) Tj
T*
(- no cached Docker builder image with --no-build: rerun without --no-build once.) Tj
T*
(- GUI bootstrap popup failed: run python build.py --network <mainnet|testnet|regnet> in terminal) Tj
T*
(to inspect direct output.) Tj
T*
(- If native runtime fails after bootstrap, inspect local logs and run:) Tj
T*
(- python Src/Main/runnode.py) Tj
T*
(- python Src/Main/stop.py --all --include-launcher) Tj
T*
ET
